Observations on the letter written to Sir Thomas Osborn, upon the reading of a book called The present interest of England stated written in a letter to a friend. Bethel, Slingsby, 1617-1697. Leeds, Thomas Osborne, Duke of, 1631-1712. Lisola, François Paul, baron de, 1613-1674. Holles, Denzil Holles, Baron, 1599-1680.
[2], 20 p.
Printed for J.B., London : 1673.
Reproduction of original in Huntington Library. "April 17th. anno 1669 ..." [p.18-20] is an opinion by Denzel Holles concerning the case of Sir Francis Toppe. cf. Huntington Library. Attributed to Slingsby Bethel. cf. BM. Attributed by Wing to François Paul de Lisola.
